# State Machine Implementation

Skill for implementing finite state machines (FSM) for NPC AI, game logic, and entity behaviors in SCPB.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Creating NPC AI with multiple states
- Implementing game entity behaviors
- Building game event systems
- Managing entity lifecycle
- Handling complex AI transitions

## Basic State Machine

### State Machine Framework

```blitzbasic
; State Machine Framework for SCPB

; State constants
Const STATE_INVALID% = -1
Const STATE_IDLE% = 0
Const STATE_ACTIVE% = 1
Const STATE_ALERT% = 2
Const STATE_ATTACK% = 3
Const STATE_FLEE% = 4
Const STATE_DEAD% = 5

; Transition types
Const TRANSITION_NORMAL% = 0
Const TRANSITION_FORCED% = 1
Const TRANSITION_INSTANT% = 2

; State machine type
Type StateMachine
    Field Owner%         ; Entity that owns this SM
    Field CurrentState%
    Field PreviousState%
    Field StateTimer#    ; Time in current state
    Field StateTimerMax# ; Max time in state (for timed states)
    Field Transition%    ; Current transition type
    Field Transitions%[20] ; Transition table
End Type

Function CreateStateMachine%(owner%)
    sm.StateMachine = New StateMachine
    sm\Owner = owner
    sm\CurrentState = STATE_IDLE
    sm\PreviousState = STATE_INVALID
    sm\StateTimer = 0
    sm\Transition = TRANSITION_NORMAL
    Return Handle(sm)
End Function
```

### State Management

```blitzbasic
; Change state with transition
Function StateMachine_ChangeState%(sm.StateMachine, newState%)
    If sm = Null Then Return False

    ; Call exit function for current state
    StateMachine_OnExit(sm, sm\CurrentState)

    ; Update history
    sm\PreviousState = sm\CurrentState
    sm\CurrentState = newState
    sm\StateTimer = 0

    ; Call entry function for new state
    StateMachine_OnEnter(sm, newState)

    Return True
End Function

; Timed state change
Function StateMachine_SetTimedState%(sm.StateMachine, newState%, duration#)
    sm\StateTimerMax = duration
    StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, newState)
End Function

; Check if in state
Function StateMachine_InState%(sm.StateMachine, state%)
    Return sm\CurrentState = state
End Function

; Check if was in state
Function StateMachine_WasInState%(sm.StateMachine, state%)
    Return sm\PreviousState = state
End Function

; Get time in state
Function StateMachine_GetStateTime#(sm.StateMachine)
    Return sm\StateTimer
End Function

; Get state progress (0.0 to 1.0)
Function StateMachine_GetStateProgress#(sm.StateMachine)
    If sm\StateTimerMax = 0 Then Return 1.0
    Return Min(sm\StateTimer / sm\StateTimerMax, 1.0)
End Function
```

### State Update Loop

```blitzbasic
; Update state machine each frame
Function StateMachine_Update%(sm.StateMachine)
    If sm = Null Then Return False

    ; Update timer
    sm\StateTimer = sm\StateTimer + 1

    ; Update current state behavior
    StateMachine_UpdateState(sm, sm\CurrentState)

    ; Check for transitions
    StateMachine_CheckTransitions(sm)

    Return True
End Function

; State behavior update
Function StateMachine_UpdateState%(sm.StateMachine, state%)
    Select state
        Case STATE_IDLE
            StateMachine_UpdateIdle(sm)
        Case STATE_ACTIVE
            StateMachine_UpdateActive(sm)
        Case STATE_ALERT
            StateMachine_UpdateAlert(sm)
        Case STATE_ATTACK
            StateMachine_UpdateAttack(sm)
        Case STATE_FLEE
            StateMachine_UpdateFlee(sm)
        Case STATE_DEAD
            StateMachine_UpdateDead(sm)
    End Select
End Function
```

## NPC State Machine

### NPC State Machine Implementation

```blitzbasic
; Create NPC with state machine
Function CreateNPCWithStateMachine%(type%, parent% = 0)
    npc.NPCs = New NPCs
    npc\NPCtype = type
    npc\ID = GetUniqueNPCID()

    ; Create state machine
    npc\StateMachine = CreateStateMachine(Handle(npc))

    ; Load mesh
    npc\obj = LoadAnimMesh("GFX/npcs/" + NPCFilename$(type) + ".b3d")
    npc\Collider = LoadMesh("GFX/npcs/" + NPCFilename$(type) + "_col.b3d")

    ; Initialize state
    StateMachine_ChangeState(npc\StateMachine, STATE_IDLE)

    Return Handle(npc)
End Function

; Update NPC with state machine
Function UpdateNPCStateMachine%(npc.NPCs)
    If npc = Null Then Return False

    ; Update state machine
    StateMachine_Update(npc\StateMachine)

    ; Update animation based on state
    UpdateNPCAnimation(npc)

    ; Update movement
    UpdateNPCMovement(npc)

    Return True
End Function
```

### State Behaviors

```blitzbasic
; IDLE state
Function StateMachine_UpdateIdle%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Check for player detection
    If CanSeePlayer(owner) Or CanHearPlayer(owner)
        StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ALERT)
        Return
    End If

    ; Random wander
    sm\StateTimer = sm\StateTimer + 1
    If sm\StateTimer > 300  ; 5 seconds
        sm\StateTimer = 0
        If Rand(1, 100) < 30
            StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ACTIVE)
        End If
    End If
End Function

; ACTIVE state
Function StateMachine_UpdateActive%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Wander
    Wander(owner)

    ; Check for player
    If CanSeePlayer(owner) Or CanHearPlayer(owner)
        StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ALERT)
    End If
End Function

; ALERT state
Function StateMachine_UpdateAlert%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Investigate or attack
    If CanSeePlayer(owner)
        StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ATTACK)
    ElseIf CanHearPlayer(owner)
        InvestigateSound(owner)
    Else
        ; Lost player, search briefly
        sm\StateTimer = sm\StateTimer + 1
        If sm\StateTimer > 180  ; 3 seconds search
            StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ACTIVE)
        End If
    End If
End Function

; ATTACK state
Function StateMachine_UpdateAttack%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Move to attack range
    dist# = Distance(owner\obj, PlayerCollider)

    If dist > 3.0
        MoveTowards(owner, PlayerCollider, owner\Speed)
    Else
        ; Attack
        PerformAttack(owner)
    End If

    ; Flee if low health
    If owner\Health < owner\MaxHealth * 0.3
        If Rand(1, 100) < 10
            StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_FLEE)
        End If
    End If
End Function

; FLEE state
Function StateMachine_UpdateFlee%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Run away from player
    FleeFromPlayer(owner)

    ; Stop when far enough
    If Distance(owner\obj, PlayerCollider) > 30.0
        StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, STATE_ACTIVE)
    End If

    ; Recover health when safe
    sm\StateTimer = sm\StateTimer + 1
    If sm\StateTimer > 600  ; 10 seconds
        owner\Health = Min(owner\Health + 1, owner\MaxHealth)
    End If
End Function

; DEAD state
Function StateMachine_UpdateDead%(sm.StateMachine)
    ; No update needed for dead NPCs
End Function
```

### State Transitions

```blitzbasic
; Define transition table
Function StateMachine_DefineTransitions%(sm.StateMachine)
    ; From STATE_IDLE
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_IDLE, STATE_ACTIVE, "timer")
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_IDLE, STATE_ALERT, "detect")

    ; From STATE_ACTIVE
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ACTIVE, STATE_IDLE, "timer")
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ACTIVE, STATE_ALERT, "detect")

    ; From STATE_ALERT
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ALERT, STATE_ATTACK, "see")
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ALERT, STATE_ACTIVE, "lost")

    ; From STATE_ATTACK
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ATTACK, STATE_FLEE, "low_health")
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_ATTACK, STATE_ALERT, "lose_sight")

    ; From STATE_FLEE
    AddTransition(sm, STATE_FLEE, STATE_ACTIVE, "safe")
End Function

; Check transitions each frame
Function StateMachine_CheckTransitions%(sm.StateMachine)
    owner.NPCs = Object.NPCs(sm\Owner)

    ; Check all possible transitions from current state
    transitions$ = GetTransitions(sm\CurrentState)

    ForEach transition$ in transitions$
        If EvaluateTransitionCondition(owner, transition$)
            nextState = GetTransitionTarget(sm\CurrentState, transition$)
            StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, nextState)
            Return
        End If
    Next
End Function

Function EvaluateTransitionCondition%(owner.NPCs, transition$)
    Select transition$
        Case "timer"
            Return Rand(1, 100) < 30

        Case "detect"
            Return CanSeePlayer(owner) Or CanHearPlayer(owner)

        Case "see"
            Return CanSeePlayer(owner)

        Case "lost"
            Return Not CanSeePlayer(owner) And Not CanHearPlayer(owner)

        Case "low_health"
            Return owner\Health < owner\MaxHealth * 0.3

        Case "safe"
            Return Distance(owner\obj, PlayerCollider) > 30.0

        Case "lose_sight"
            Return Not CanSeePlayer(owner)

        Default
            Return False
    End Select
End Function
```

## HFSM (Hierarchical FSM)

```blitzbasic
; Hierarchical FSM for complex behaviors

Type HFSM_State
    Field Name$
    Field Parent%        ; Parent state index (-1 for root)
    Field OnEnter%       ; Function to call on enter
    Field OnUpdate%      ; Function to call on update
    Field OnExit%       ; Function to call on exit
    Field SubStates%[10] ; Child states
    Field DefaultSub%    ; Default substate
    Field CurrentSub%    ; Current substate
End Type

Type HFSM
    Field States[20]     ; State definitions
    Field StateCount%
    Field CurrentState%
    Field CurrentSub%
End Type

Function CreateHFSM%()
    hfsm.HFSM = New HFSM
    hfsm\StateCount = 0
    hfsm\CurrentState = -1
    hfsm\CurrentSub = -1
    Return Handle(hfsm)
End Function

Function HFSM_AddState%(hfsm.HFSM, name$, parent% = -1)
    index = hfsm\StateCount
    hfsm\States[index]\Name = name$
    hfsm\States[index]\Parent = parent
    hfsm\States[index]\CurrentSub = -1
    hfsm\StateCount = index + 1
    Return index
End Function

Function HFSM_EnterState%(hfsm.HFSM, state%)
    ; Exit current substate
    If hfsm\CurrentSub >= 0
        HFSM_ExitState(hfsm, hfsm\States[hfsm\States[state]\CurrentSub])
    End If

    ; Exit current state
    If hfsm\CurrentState >= 0
        HFSM_ExitState(hfsm, hfsm\States[hfsm\CurrentState])
    End If

    ; Enter new state
    hfsm\CurrentState = state
    hfsm\CurrentSub = hfsm\States[state]\DefaultSub

    If hfsm\CurrentSub >= 0
        HFSM_EnterState(hfsm, hfsm\States[hfsm\CurrentSub])
    End If

    HFSM_EnterState(hfsm, hfsm\States[state])
End Function

Function HFSM_Update%(hfsm.HFSM)
    If hfsm\CurrentState < 0 Then Return

    ; Update current substate
    If hfsm\CurrentSub >= 0
        HFSM_UpdateState(hfsm, hfsm\States[hfsm\States[hfsm\CurrentState]\CurrentSub])
    End If

    ; Update current state
    HFSM_UpdateState(hfsm, hfsm\States[hfsm\CurrentState])

    ; Check for state transitions
    HFSM_CheckTransitions(hfsm)
End Function
```

## Behavior Tree Integration

```blitzbasic
; Simple behavior tree nodes for AI

Type BT_Node
    Field Type%          ; 0=Sequence, 1=Selector, 2=Action, 3=Condition
    Field Children[10]   ; Child nodes
    Field ChildCount%
    Field Result%        ; 0=Running, 1=Success, 2=Failure
    Field Name$
End Type

Const BT_SEQUENCE% = 0
Const BT_SELECTOR% = 1
Const BT_ACTION% = 2
Const BT_CONDITION% = 3

Function BT_Create%(type%, name$ = "")
    node.BT_Node = New BT_Node
    node\Type = type$
    node\Name = name$
    node\ChildCount = 0
    node\Result = 0
    Return Handle(node)
End Function

Function BT_AddChild%(parent.BT_Node, child.BT_Node)
    parent\Children[parent\ChildCount] = Handle(child)
    parent\ChildCount = parent\ChildCount + 1
End Function

Function BT_Run%(node.BT_Node)
    Select node\Type
        Case BT_SEQUENCE
            Return BT_RunSequence(node)
        Case BT_SELECTOR
            Return BT_RunSelector(node)
        Case BT_ACTION
            Return BT_RunAction(node)
        Case BT_CONDITION
            Return BT_RunCondition(node)
    End Select
End Function

Function BT_RunSequence%(node.BT_Node)
    For i = 0 To node\ChildCount - 1
        child.BT_Node = Object.BT_Node(node\Children[i])
        result = BT_Run(child)
        If result = 2  ; Failure
            node\Result = 2
            Return 2
        End If
    Next
    node\Result = 1  ; All children succeeded
    Return 1
End Function

Function BT_RunSelector%(node.BT_Node)
    For i = 0 To node\ChildCount - 1
        child.BT_Node = Object.BT_Node(node\Children[i])
        result = BT_Run(child)
        If result = 1  ; Success
            node\Result = 1
            Return 1
        End If
    Next
    node\Result = 2  ; All children failed
    Return 2
End Function
```

## NPC State Debug

```blitzbasic
Function Debug_StateMachine(npc.NPCs)
    If npc = Null Then Return

    sm = npc\StateMachine
    If sm = 0 Then Return

    Debug_Print "=== STATE MACHINE ==="
    Debug_Print "Current: " + GetStateName(sm\CurrentState)
    Debug_Print "Previous: " + GetStateName(sm\PreviousState)
    Debug_Print "Time: " + sm\StateTimer + " frames"
    Debug_Print "Progress: " + Int(StateMachine_GetStateProgress(sm) * 100) + "%"

    ; Possible transitions
    Debug_Print "Transitions:"
    transitions$ = GetTransitions(sm\CurrentState)
    ForEach t$ in transitions$
        If EvaluateTransitionCondition(npc, t$)
            Debug_Print "  -> " + GetStateName(GetTransitionTarget(sm\CurrentState, t$)) + " (READY)"
        Else
            Debug_Print "  -> " + GetStateName(GetTransitionTarget(sm\CurrentState, t$)) + " (blocked)"
        End If
    Next
End Function
```

## Quick Reference

| State | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `STATE_IDLE` | Wait, no activity |
| `STATE_ACTIVE` | Normal activity |
| `STATE_ALERT` | Noticed something |
| `STATE_ATTACK` | Engaging target |
| `STATE_FLEE` | Escaping danger |
| `STATE_DEAD` | No longer active |

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `CreateStateMachine(owner)` | Create FSM for entity |
| `StateMachine_ChangeState(sm, state)` | Change to new state |
| `StateMachine_Update(sm)` | Update FSM each frame |
| `StateMachine_InState(sm, state)` | Check current state |
| `StateMachine_GetStateTime(sm)` | Get time in current state |
